    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Millinery pieces that cover only a small part of the head, the front edge beginning above the hairline, and resting on the crown. Originally developed by Lilly Daché ca. 1940, these may be embellished with a variety of decorative elements.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
